name: Greeting Cards
description:
Hamsa meaning "five", is a hand shaped amulet, popular throughout the Middle East and North Arica. The Hamsa is usually stylized with two symmetrical thumbs, with the fingers pointing either up or down. The Hamsa is considered to be a sign of protection that wards off evil and that can lead to good fortune and personal well-being.

The Dove, a universal symbol for peace, has been combined with the Hamsa to form one symbol, which is the current logo for the Yonim Israeli Folk Dancers of Madison, WI. This logo has been designed further for a series of greeting cards, with a portion of each sale being donated to dancers, enabling them to attend annual Folk Dance Camps.

Each set includes 6 cards (4.25x5.50): Happy Birthday (2), Mazel Tov, Shalom, Congratulations, Thank You

name: Bag Tag | Abstract
description:
These Bag Tags represent Ruth Fromstein’s original works of art, using a variety of mediums. They are playful and eye catching, with designs that appeal to every age and lifestyle. Artistic Bag Tags make wonderful gifts, party favors and stocking stuffers for oneself and others.

ID your backpack, luggage, lunchbox or sports bag with personality!
Bag Tags measure 2"x3.25". Hanging loop included.

Wholesale pricing available.
